{"word":"εὐανθής","slug":"εὐανθής","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>εὐανθής</b></el> <el>(εὐ-ανθής, ές) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><el>ἄνθος</el>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>blooming, budding</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>rich in flowers, flowery</i>, <b><a href='S:Theognis'>Theogn.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>flowered, gay-coloured, gay, bright</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>III. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>blooming, fresh, goodly</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}